    <string name="FAQ_HelpTitle"><u><b>FAQ</b></u></string>
    <string name="Help_Q1">Q:Events &amp; Festivals isn\'t loading, what\'s wrong?</string>
    <string name="Help_A1">A:Event Tracker requires an internet connection to provide up-to-date events.</string>
    <string name="Help_Q2">Q:I have an internet connection and it still isn\'t loading, what do I do? </string>
    <string name="Help_A2">A:Event Tracker requires a stable internet connection, it could be a problem in your area.
                            Contact support at vmmirabella@myseneca.ca if the problem persists.</string>
    <string name="Help_Q3">Q:How do I track an event I would like to go to? </string>
    <string name="Help_A3">A:On the Events &amp; Festivals page you can click an event to view more details about it.
                            On the details page there is a \'Track\' button in the top right if you wish to track it.</string>
    <string name="Help_Q4">Q:I wish to edit/delete an event on My Events, how do I do it?</string>
    <string name="Help_A4">A:On the My Events page you can select Edit or Delete by performing a long click(hold for 1â€“2 seconds) on the desired event. Only events you have created can be edited.</string>
    <string name="Help_Q5">Q:Is there a way to turn notifications off?</string>
    <string name="Help_A5">A:Yes, you can turn off notifications by opening the menu, select Settings and switching \'Notification\' to off</string>
    <string name="Help_Q6">Q:I don\'t like the default theme, is there a way to change it?</string>
    <string name="Help_A6">A:Yes, you can switch between dark and light themes in Settings</string>

